events.description: Yazid I's army kills 11,000 people of Medina including notable Sahabas in Battle of al-Harrah.
events.html: • 683 – Yazid I's army kills 11,000 people of Medina including notable Sahabas in Battle of al-Harrah.

events.description: The Seljuq Turks defeat the Byzantine army at the Battle of Manzikert, and soon gain control of most of Anatolia.
events.html: • 1071 – The Seljuq Turks defeat the Byzantine army at the Battle of Manzikert, and soon gain control of most of Anatolia.

events.description: Ladislaus IV of Hungary and Rudolf I of Germany defeat Ottokar II of Bohemia in the Battle on the Marchfeld near Dürnkrut in (then) Moravia.
events.html: • 1278 – Ladislaus IV of Hungary and Rudolf I of Germany defeat Ottokar II of Bohemia in the Battle on the Marchfeld near Dürnkrut in (then) Moravia.

events.description: Chittorgarh falls to the Delhi Sultanate.
events.html: • 1303 – Chittorgarh falls to the Delhi Sultanate.

events.description: At the Battle of Crécy, an English army easily defeats a French one twice its size.
events.html: • 1346 – At the Battle of Crécy, an English army easily defeats a French one twice its size.

events.description: Battle of St. Jakob an der Birs: A vastly outnumbered force of Swiss Confederates is defeated by the Dauphin Louis (future Louis XI of France) and his army of 'Armagnacs' near Basel.
events.html: • 1444 – Battle of St. Jakob an der Birs: A vastly outnumbered force of Swiss Confederates is defeated by the Dauphin Louis (future Louis XI of France) and his army of 'Armagnacs' near Basel.

entities.name: Battle of St. Jakob an der Birs

events.description: Francisco de Orellana crosses South America from Guayaquil on the Pacific coast to the mouth of the Amazon River on the Atlantic coast.
events.html: • 1542 – Francisco de Orellana crosses South America from Guayaquil on the Pacific coast to the mouth of the Amazon River on the Atlantic coast.

events.description: Dutch–Portuguese War: Second Battle of San Salvador: The Dutch force the Spanish garrison at San Salvador (modern day Keelung, Taiwan) to surrender, ending the short-lived Spanish colony on Formosa and replacing it with a new Dutch administration.
events.html: • 1642 – Dutch–Portuguese War: Second Battle of San Salvador: The Dutch force the Spanish garrison at San Salvador (modern day Keelung, Taiwan) to surrender, ending the short-lived Spanish colony on Formosa and replacing it with a new Dutch administration.[1]

events.description: The Fronde: First Fronde: In the wake of the successful Battle of Lens, Cardinal Mazarin, Chief Minister of France, suddenly orders the arrest of the leaders of the Parlement of Paris, provoking the rest of Paris to break into insurrection and barricade the streets the next day.
events.html: • 1648 – The Fronde: First Fronde: In the wake of the successful Battle of Lens, Cardinal Mazarin, Chief Minister of France, suddenly orders the arrest of the leaders of the Parlement of Paris, provoking the rest of Paris to break into insurrection and barricade the streets the next day.[2]

events.description: The first Lutheran denomination in North America, the Pennsylvania Ministerium, is founded in Philadelphia.
events.html: • 1748 – The first Lutheran denomination in North America, the Pennsylvania Ministerium, is founded in Philadelphia.

events.description: Jesuits all over Chile are arrested as the Spanish Empire suppresses the Society of Jesus.
events.html: • 1767 – Jesuits all over Chile are arrested as the Spanish Empire suppresses the Society of Jesus.[3]

entities.name: Suppression of the Society of Jesus

events.description: Captain James Cook sets sail from England on board HMS Endeavour.
events.html: • 1768 – Captain James Cook sets sail from England on board HMS Endeavour.

events.description: The first recorded ascent of Triglav, the highest mountain in Slovenia.
events.html: • 1778 – The first recorded ascent of Triglav, the highest mountain in Slovenia.

events.description: The Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen is approved by the National Constituent Assembly of France.
events.html: • 1789 – The Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen is approved by the National Constituent Assembly of France.

entities.name: Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen

events.description: John Fitch is granted a United States patent for the steamboat.
events.html: • 1791 – John Fitch is granted a United States patent for the steamboat.

events.description: The former viceroy Santiago de Liniers of the Viceroyalty of the Río de la Plata is executed after the defeat of his counter-revolution.
events.html: • 1810 – The former viceroy Santiago de Liniers of the Viceroyalty of the Río de la Plata is executed after the defeat of his counter-revolution.

entities.name: Viceroyalty of the Río de la Plata

events.description: War of the Sixth Coalition: An impromptu battle takes place when French and Prussian-Russian forces accidentally run into each other near Liegnitz, Prussia (now Legnica, Poland).
events.html: • 1813 – War of the Sixth Coalition: An impromptu battle takes place when French and Prussian-Russian forces accidentally run into each other near Liegnitz, Prussia (now Legnica, Poland).

events.description: Chilean War of Independence: Infighting between the rebel forces of José Miguel Carrera and Bernardo O'Higgins erupts in the Battle of Las Tres Acequias.
events.html: • 1814 – Chilean War of Independence: Infighting between the rebel forces of José Miguel Carrera and Bernardo O'Higgins erupts in the Battle of Las Tres Acequias.

events.description: The great 1833 Kathmandu–Bihar earthquake causes major damage in Nepal, northern India and Tibet, a total of 500 people perish.
events.html: • 1833 – The great 1833 Kathmandu–Bihar earthquake causes major damage in Nepal, northern India and Tibet, a total of 500 people perish.[4]

events.description: President Faustin Soulouque of the First Republic of Haiti has the Senate and Chamber of Deputies proclaim him the Emperor of Haiti, abolishing the Republic and inaugurating the Second Empire of Haiti.
events.html: • 1849 – President Faustin Soulouque of the First Republic of Haiti has the Senate and Chamber of Deputies proclaim him the Emperor of Haiti, abolishing the Republic and inaugurating the Second Empire of Haiti.[5]

events.description: The Swedish-language liberal newspaper Helsingfors Dagblad proposed the current blue-and-white cross flag as the flag of Finland.
events.html: • 1863 – The Swedish-language liberal newspaper Helsingfors Dagblad proposed the current blue-and-white cross flag as the flag of Finland.[6]

events.description: The 1883 eruption of Krakatoa begins its final, paroxysmal, stage.
events.html: • 1883 – The 1883 eruption of Krakatoa begins its final, paroxysmal, stage.

events.description: World War I: The German colony of Togoland surrenders to French and British forces after a 20-day campaign. Togoland is the first German colony to fall to Allied hands in World War I.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: The German colony of Togoland surrenders to French and British forces after a 20-day campaign. Togoland is the first German colony to fall to Allied hands in World War I.

events.description: World War I: During the retreat from Mons, the British II Corps commanded by General Sir Horace Smith-Dorrien fights a vigorous and successful defensive action at Le Cateau.
events.html: • 1914 – World War I: During the retreat from Mons, the British II Corps commanded by General Sir Horace Smith-Dorrien fights a vigorous and successful defensive action at Le Cateau.

events.description: The 19th amendment to United States Constitution, giving women the right to vote, is certified.
events.html: • 1920 – The 19th amendment to United States Constitution, giving women the right to vote, is certified.

entities.name: Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution

events.description: Greco-Turkish War (1919–22): Turkish army launched what has come to be known to the Turks as the Great Offensive (Büyük Taarruz). The major Greek defense positions were overrun.
events.html: • 1922 – Greco-Turkish War (1919–22): Turkish army launched what has come to be known to the Turks as the Great Offensive (Büyük Taarruz). The major Greek defense positions were overrun.

events.description: Spanish Civil War: Santander falls to the nationalists and the republican interprovincial council is dissolved.
events.html: • 1936 – Spanish Civil War: Santander falls to the nationalists and the republican interprovincial council is dissolved.[7]

entities.name: Interprovincial Council of Santander, Palencia and Burgos

events.description: World War II: Chad becomes the first French colony to join the Allies under the administration of Félix Éboué, France's first black colonial governor.
events.html: • 1940 – World War II: Chad becomes the first French colony to join the Allies under the administration of Félix Éboué, France's first black colonial governor.

events.description: The Holocaust in Ukraine: At Chortkiv, the Ukrainian police and German Schutzpolizei deport two thousand Jews to Bełżec extermination camp. Five hundred of the sick and children are murdered on the spot. This continued until the next day.
events.html: • 1942 – The Holocaust in Ukraine: At Chortkiv, the Ukrainian police and German Schutzpolizei deport two thousand Jews to Bełżec extermination camp. Five hundred of the sick and children are murdered on the spot. This continued until the next day.

events.description: World War II: Charles de Gaulle enters Paris.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: Charles de Gaulle enters Paris.

events.description: The South African Border War starts with the battle at Omugulugwombashe.
events.html: • 1966 – The South African Border War starts with the battle at Omugulugwombashe.

events.description: Aeroflot Flight 1770 crashes while landing at Vnukovo International Airport, killing 16.
events.html: • 1969 – Aeroflot Flight 1770 crashes while landing at Vnukovo International Airport, killing 16.[8]

events.description: The fiftieth anniversary of American women being able to vote is marked by a nationwide Women's Strike for Equality.
events.html: • 1970 – The fiftieth anniversary of American women being able to vote is marked by a nationwide Women's Strike for Equality.

events.description: The Games of the XX Olympiad open in Munich, West Germany.
events.html: • 1972 – The Games of the XX Olympiad open in Munich, West Germany.[9]

events.description: The Charter of the French Language is adopted by the National Assembly of Quebec.
events.html: • 1977 – The Charter of the French Language is adopted by the National Assembly of Quebec.

events.description: Papal conclave: Albino Luciani is elected as Pope John Paul I.
events.html: • 1978 – Papal conclave: Albino Luciani is elected as Pope John Paul I.

events.description: After John Birges plants a bomb at Harvey's Resort Hotel in Stateline, Nevada, in the United States, the FBI inadvertently detonates the bomb during its disarming.
events.html: • 1980 – After John Birges plants a bomb at Harvey's Resort Hotel in Stateline, Nevada, in the United States, the FBI inadvertently detonates the bomb during its disarming.

events.description: Sakha Avia Flight 301 crashes on approach to Aldan Airport, killing all 24 aboard.
events.html: • 1993 – Sakha Avia Flight 301 crashes on approach to Aldan Airport, killing all 24 aboard.[10]

events.description: Beni Ali massacre occurs in Algeria, leaving 60 to 100 people dead.
events.html: • 1997 – Beni Ali massacre occurs in Algeria, leaving 60 to 100 people dead.

events.description: The first flight of the Boeing Delta III ends in disaster 75 seconds after liftoff resulting in the loss of the Galaxy X  communications satellite.
events.html: • 1998 – The first flight of the Boeing Delta III ends in disaster 75 seconds after liftoff resulting in the loss of the Galaxy X communications satellite.

events.description: Russia begins the Second Chechen War in response to the Invasion of Dagestan by the Islamic International Peacekeeping Brigade.
events.html: • 1999 – Russia begins the Second Chechen War in response to the Invasion of Dagestan by the Islamic International Peacekeeping Brigade.

events.description: A Beechcraft 1900 operating as Colgan Air Flight 9446 crashes after taking off from Barnstable Municipal Airport in Yarmouth, Massachusetts, killing both pilots on board.
events.html: • 2003 – A Beechcraft 1900 operating as Colgan Air Flight 9446 crashes after taking off from Barnstable Municipal Airport in Yarmouth, Massachusetts, killing both pilots on board.[11]

events.description: Kidnapping victim Jaycee Dugard is discovered alive in California after being missing for over 18 years. Her captors, Phillip and Nancy Garrido are apprehended.
events.html: • 2009 – Kidnapping victim Jaycee Dugard is discovered alive in California after being missing for over 18 years. Her captors, Phillip and Nancy Garrido are apprehended.

events.description: The Boeing 787 Dreamliner, Boeing's all-new composite airliner, receives certification from the EASA and the FAA.
events.html: • 2011 – The Boeing 787 Dreamliner, Boeing's all-new composite airliner, receives certification from the EASA and the FAA.

events.description: The Jay Report into the Rotherham child sexual exploitation scandal is published.
events.html: • 2014 – The Jay Report into the Rotherham child sexual exploitation scandal is published.[12]

events.description: Two U.S. journalists are shot and killed by a disgruntled former coworker while conducting a live report in Moneta, Virginia.
events.html: • 2015 – Two U.S. journalists are shot and killed by a disgruntled former coworker while conducting a live report in Moneta, Virginia.

entities.name: Murders of Alison Parker and Adam Ward

events.description: Three people are killed and eleven wounded during a mass shooting at a Madden NFL '19 video game tournament in Jacksonville, Florida.
events.html: • 2018 – Three people are killed and eleven wounded during a mass shooting at a Madden NFL '19 video game tournament in Jacksonville, Florida.[13]

events.description: During the 2021 Kabul airlift, a suicide bombing at Hamid Karzai International Airport kills 13 US military personnel and at least 169 Afghan civilians.
events.html: • 2021 – During the 2021 Kabul airlift, a suicide bombing at Hamid Karzai International Airport kills 13 US military personnel and at least 169 Afghan civilians.[14]

events.description: Exactly 5 years after the 2018 Jacksonville Landing shooting, there is another shooting in Jacksonville, Florida, leaving 3 people dead.
events.html: • 2023 – Exactly 5 years after the 2018 Jacksonville Landing shooting, there is another shooting in Jacksonville, Florida, leaving 3 people dead.[15]
